From 320ee3c58a8a49c82f450f979f6359c6f853473e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:49:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: rk3576-generic: give autoboot an interruptible
 delay

Set CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=10. This build autoboots, but leaves a window wide
enough to reach the prompt from either console.

Ten seconds is chosen for the HDMI path, not the serial one. A television
or AV receiver takes roughly two to five seconds to lock a newly active
source and put pixels on screen, so a conventional two- or three-second
delay expires before the operator can see that there is anything to
interrupt -- which defeats the whole point of a display-carrying rescue
build. Serial users pay the extra seconds; they are the ones who least
need them.

The board keeps no persistent u-boot environment ("Loading Environment
from nowhere"), so the delay cannot be adjusted at runtime and has to be
correct at build time.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
index 3a6044b5..ab3d4f14 100644
--- a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
+++ b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
@@ -9,6 +9,7 @@ CONFIG_SYS_LOAD_ADDR=0x40c00800
 CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_BASE=0x2AD40000
 CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_CLOCK=24000000
 CONFIG_DEBUG_UART=y
+CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=10
 # CONFIG_BOOTMETH_VBE is not set
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_FDT_FILE="rockchip/rk3576-generic.dtb"
 # CONFIG_DISPLAY_CPUINFO is not set
-- 
